definition:510B:
\paragraph{Context}
General linear methods are defined by matrices $(A,U,B,V)$ for solving ODEs. Preconsistency requires a vector $u$ such that
\begin{align}
V u &= u, \tag{510a}\\
U u &= \mathbf{1}, \tag{510b}
\end{align}
where $\mathbf{1}$ is the vector of all ones. Consistency adds a vector $v$ satisfying $B\mathbf{1} + V v = u + v$, related to second-order accuracy.

definition:510C:
\paragraph{Context}
