\end{equation}
Let $z = hq$, where $h$ is the stepsize. The numerical solution propagates as
\begin{equation}
    y^{[n]} = M(z) y^{[n-1]}, \tag{520b}
\end{equation}
where $M(z)$ is the $r \times r$ stability matrix. The stability function and region are defined via the characteristic polynomial of $M(z)$ and the boundedness of its powers.

theorem:520D:
