theorem:535A:
\paragraph{Context}
Consider a consistent general linear method $(A,U,B,V)$ with $u=e_1$, where $U$ and $V$ have block structures
\[
U=\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&U_{22}\end{bmatrix},\qquad V=\begin{bmatrix}1&0\\0&V_{22}\end{bmatrix}.
\]
Let $e_1$ be the first natural basis vector in $\mathbb{R}^r$. For a given underlying one‑step method $\theta$, define $\eta$ and $\xi$ by
\begin{align}
